  <section id="running_at_spi_validator">
      <title>Running the AT-SPI Validator Plugin</title>
      <p>
        To run the AT-SPI Validator Plugin, select an item in the desktop tree view PENDING (link to 
        a section that explains this tree). This item can either be a target application 
        or one of its widgets. The validator will generate the report with respect to
        the selected item and all of its descendant widgets in the tree hierarchy.
      </p>
      <figure>
        <title>Selecting an item in the desktop tree view</title>
    <desc>
      To run the AT-SPI Validator Plugin, select either an application or one of its widgets in the
      desktop tree view.
    </desc>
    <media type="image" mime="image/png" width="800" height="500" src="figures/accessible_tree.png">
      <p>
        To run the AT-SPI Validator Plugin, select either an application or one of its widgets in the
        desktop tree view.
      </p>
    </media>
  </figure>


      <p>
        After selecting an item in the desktop tree view, choose a validation schema in the combobox 
        and press the <cmd>Validate</cmd> button to start generating the report. If you want to cancel
        the execution, just press the <cmd>Validate</cmd> button again.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you want to save the generated report in your system, just click the <cmd>Save</cmd> button.
        To clear the validation screen, you just need to press the <cmd>Clear</cmd> button.
      </p>
